1
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:02,320
Miss Jiang.

2
00:02:02,920 --> 00:02:04,920
I understand how you feel right now.

3
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:06,720
My condolences.

4
00:02:09,120 --> 00:02:11,280
There are still many suspicious points about the case.

5
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:15,440
I'm afraid you can't take Mr. Mu's body back yet.

6
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:17,960
Suspicious points?

7
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:20,320
What suspicious points?

8
00:02:20,720 --> 00:02:23,280
Didn't he die of a sudden heart attack?

9
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:27,600
We need to perform a further autopsy on the body

10
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:30,160
to find out the truth of the case.

11
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:31,960
We hope for your full cooperation.

12
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:33,079
An autopsy?

13
00:02:33,640 --> 00:02:34,800
Why an autopsy?

14
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,000
Come take a look.

15
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:41,320
This...

16
00:02:41,600 --> 00:02:43,560
I won't allow my husband to be treated like this.

17
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:45,200
He is already dead.

18
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:47,250
I just want him to rest in peace.

19
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:50,040
If you really want him to rest in peace,

20
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:51,640
we need to find out the truth.

21
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:52,880
I am sure you don't want

22
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:55,210
Mr. Mu's death to remain a mystery, do you?

23
00:02:56,520 --> 00:02:58,000
Are you saying

24
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,760
he was murdered?

25
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,960
We currently have our suspicions.

26
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,040
Suspicions?

27
00:03:04,880 --> 00:03:07,120
Just for an unconfirmed suspicion,

28
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:09,520
you want to cut him open?

29
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:10,880
Officer Zhuang,

30
00:03:10,880 --> 00:03:12,360
he is already gone.

31
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:15,290
I don't want him to suffer in this cold place anymore.

32
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:18,760
As his wife,

33
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:21,280
this is my only request.

34
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:39,320
Why bother?

35
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:42,370
They had such a good relationship,

36
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:44,440
why would they separate?

37
00:03:44,760 --> 00:03:46,200
Do you really think so?

38
00:03:48,440 --> 00:03:49,640
I don't understand.

39
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:51,170
That must be so painful.

40
00:03:52,880 --> 00:03:54,740
Their relationship wasn't good.

41
00:03:55,160 --> 00:03:57,400
At least not as good as she made it out to be.

42
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:58,400
Bro,

43
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:00,000
why are you sneaking around?

44
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:01,400
You scared me.

45
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:03,160
I just got here.

46
00:04:03,480 --> 00:04:05,410
Alright, you two, stop bickering.

47
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:06,360
Mo,

48
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:09,890
why do you think their relationship wasn't good?

49
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:13,520
Her formal attire

50
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:15,720
and serious demeanor

51
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:17,279
precisely indicate

52
00:04:17,279 --> 00:04:18,680
that subconsciously,

53
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:21,760
she has accepted the fact of Mu Weijie's death.

54
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:26,810
Captain Zhuang,

55
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:28,260
do you think so too?

56
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:32,760
Just a gut feeling.

57
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:35,800
This woman is so normal

58
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:37,040
that it's a bit abnormal.

59
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:38,280
Are you saying

60
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:41,280
she was faking her sadness and grief?

61
00:04:42,200 --> 00:04:43,440
It's very likely.

62
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:49,020
We need to start with the female students around Mu Weijie.

63
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:50,600
The students?

64
00:04:51,760 --> 00:04:52,640
Oh, okay.

65
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:53,240
Understood.

66
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:54,370
I'll get on it later.

67
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:56,250
Cheng Mo,

68
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:59,159
are you interested in joining us to question those students

69
00:04:59,159 --> 00:05:00,680
and see if they're lying?

70
00:05:00,960 --> 00:05:02,320
I'm not a lie detector.

71
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:05,920
Besides, during formal questioning,

72
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:07,920
people tend to get nervous under pressure,

73
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:10,400
which doesn't necessarily mean they're lying.

74
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,720
Then why are you here?

75
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:13,930
I want to go to the crime scene with you.

76
00:05:14,080 --> 00:05:16,280
I don't have time to go to the crime scene with you.

77
00:05:16,280 --> 00:05:18,410
The interrogation paperwork is done.

78
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:24,720
Go to the crime scene with him.

79
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:25,880
Leave this to me.

80
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:28,040
No problem.

81
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:32,080
Why are you so happy?

82
00:05:33,159 --> 00:05:34,320
I love my job.

83
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:36,600
Take my car.

84
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:38,760
Thank you.

85
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:40,200
Mr. Cheng, wait for me here.

86
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:41,260
I'll go get the car.

87
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:45,120
Take good care of him.

88
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:46,040
No problem.

89
00:05:49,159 --> 00:05:50,960
I can take care of myself.

90
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,920
I'm just not good at it.

91
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:59,280
Will they be okay?

92
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,720
Bai is a bit boy-crazy,

93
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:06,080
but she shouldn't act that fast.

94
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:08,520
No.

95
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:09,680
I mean,

96
00:06:09,960 --> 00:06:13,440
didn't Bai just get her driver's license?

97
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:18,800
Wish them luck.

98
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:24,520
Xiaoyue.

99
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:29,240
Will we be okay being called here so late?

100
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:30,960
It should be fine.

101
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:32,490
Just routine questioning.

102
00:06:32,640 --> 00:06:33,640
Don't be nervous.

103
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:38,680
Mr. Cheng.

104
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:40,740
What are you looking at? Let's go.

105
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:43,280
Let's go.

106
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:52,360
Xu Qiaoyue.

107
00:06:53,520 --> 00:06:54,480
No need to be nervous.

108
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:56,810
We just want to understand the situation.

109
00:06:57,800 --> 00:06:58,840
Tell me about it.

110
00:06:59,080 --> 00:07:01,400
What is your relationship with the deceased?

111
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:03,400
He was the teacher at our art studio.

112
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:04,200
Nothing more.

113
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:08,890
What kind of person do you think he was?

114
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:11,640
Mr. Mu was a very nice person.

115
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:13,160
He was an artist.

116
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:14,640
He took good care of me.

117
00:07:15,880 --> 00:07:18,840
But I never expected him to have such an accident.

118
00:07:18,840 --> 00:07:20,560
It's quite a pity.

119
00:07:22,520 --> 00:07:23,880
Why do you think

120
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:26,340
your teacher died in an accident?

121
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:31,080
Is... Isn't it?

122
00:07:31,840 --> 00:07:34,370
Isn't this the Accident Investigation Unit?

123
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:38,000
When was the last time you saw the deceased?

124
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:40,760
Thursday.

125
00:07:41,520 --> 00:07:43,050
We finished class as usual.

126
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:47,159
Mr. Mu explained the world-famous painting

127
00:07:47,159 --> 00:07:48,440
of Danaë to us that day.

128
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:50,280
He also gave us homework,

129
00:07:50,280 --> 00:07:52,200
asking us to copy the painting.

130
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:55,050
I left together with Lin Rongrong.

131
00:07:55,400 --> 00:07:57,130
I was in a hurry to return a call,

132
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:59,400
so I quickly left the studio.

133
00:07:59,640 --> 00:08:01,100
Who were you calling back?

134
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:04,450
That has nothing to do with Mr. Mu's death, right?

135
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:08,160
Just answer what you are asked.

136
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:09,220
Cooperate with us.

137
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:14,400
My boyfriend, Allen.

138
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:16,240
He called to ask me out.

139
00:08:18,120 --> 00:08:18,840
Meet up?

140
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:20,860
Where did you meet?

141
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:22,880
We are currently breaking up,

142
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,280
so I didn't meet him.

143
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:25,280
That's it.

144
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:30,500
Then who was the last to leave the studio on the day of the incident?

145
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:32,919
I was indeed the last one to leave.

146
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:35,280
But I was with Li Xinying,

147
00:08:35,280 --> 00:08:37,610
asking Mr. Mu about some sketching stuff.

148
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:39,280
Mr. Mu.

149
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:40,000
Mr. Mu.

150
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:40,799
Oh,

151
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:42,640
do we have any

152
00:08:42,919 --> 00:08:44,840
sketching plans recently?

153
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:45,920
No plans for now.

154
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:47,880
Sir,

155
00:08:47,880 --> 00:08:49,080
compared to figure painting,

156
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:51,120
we really prefer landscape painting.

157
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:51,720
Alright.

158
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,800
I'll take you guys next week.

159
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:54,440
Okay.

160
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:54,880
Okay.

161
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:56,040
Thank you, Mr. Mu.

162
00:08:56,560 --> 00:08:56,800
Thank you, Mr. Mu.

163
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:57,400
Bye.

164
00:08:58,640 --> 00:09:00,970
Then we went to the night market together.

165
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:04,560
In that case,

166
00:09:04,560 --> 00:09:05,760
after you left,

167
00:09:06,280 --> 00:09:08,120
Mu Weijie was still in the studio, right?

168
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:08,880
Yes.

169
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:12,160
Who can prove you're telling the truth?

170
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:13,200
I can.

171
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:15,250
Annie and I left together that day.

172
00:09:16,920 --> 00:09:17,850
Where did you go?

173
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:20,720
We went to the night market to buy art supplies.

174
00:09:20,720 --> 00:09:21,720
Buy art supplies?

175
00:09:22,320 --> 00:09:23,920
Oh, I still have the receipt.

176
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:28,010
Right, this one.

177
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:36,400
You like to carry receipts with you after shopping?

178
00:09:37,040 --> 00:09:38,480
Yes, I have this habit.

179
00:09:38,480 --> 00:09:40,080
I have a bunch of them at home.

180
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:43,650
Look into it carefully.

181
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:49,280
Recently,

182
00:09:49,680 --> 00:09:50,280
did you notice

183
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:52,200
any unusual behavior from Mu Weijie?

184
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:52,920
No.

185
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:55,360
Mr. Mu was the same as usual.

186
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:56,800
No unusual behavior.

187
00:09:59,880 --> 00:10:01,940
Did you know he had a heart condition?

188
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:03,320
Yes.

189
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:04,800
We all know that.

190
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:06,360
Then in the studio,

191
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:08,760
did you see him taking medicine often?

192
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:13,320
Mr. Mu usually took good care of his health.

193
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:14,800
Oh, indeed.

194
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:18,240
He took his heart medication on time every day.

195
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:21,840
What's wrong with your face?

196
00:10:23,760 --> 00:10:24,440
Oh,

197
00:10:24,920 --> 00:10:25,680
this.

198
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:28,040
When I was painting,

199
00:10:28,040 --> 00:10:30,760
I accidentally got fixative and oil paint on it.

200
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:32,140
I'm a bit allergic.

201
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:37,560
Okay.

202
00:10:37,880 --> 00:10:39,200
We'll stop here for now.

203
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:41,860
We'll contact you anytime if anything comes up.

204
00:10:41,880 --> 00:10:42,640
Okay.

205
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:56,560
How could it be so clean?

206
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:00,660
What are you doing?

207
00:11:00,840 --> 00:11:01,720
Hui.

208
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:03,640
This is the first case for our team.

209
00:11:03,640 --> 00:11:06,560
Mu Weijie's identity is special. We must handle it carefully.

210
00:11:06,560 --> 00:11:10,240
Without the family's authorization, no autopsy is allowed.

211
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:13,520
Yeah, they said to hold off on the blood test for now.

212
00:11:13,920 --> 00:11:15,680
Don't you think I know that? Wait a minute.

213
00:11:15,680 --> 00:11:17,080
Let me observe a bit more.

214
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:20,920
Help me turn him over.
